    <title>Casio Launches Trendy DENIM’D COLOR Watches</title>
    <link>http://www.techtree.com/content/news/13390/casio-launches-trendy-denim-d-color-watches.html</link>
    <description>Consumers can now rediscover their favorite denim trend with Casio’s newest launch- the DENIM’D COLOR designs. The DENIM’D COLOR variants will be a chic offering from the always tough and rugged G-SHOCK and the BABY-G casual watch for active women. The sturdy look of the G-SHOCK and the BABY-G designs is enhanced by visual jeans, one of the most preferred styles in casual fashion. The availability of both G-SHOCK and BABY-G versions means that they can be matched into his-and-her pairs. These cool designs of G-SHOCK and BABY-G models are a must-have accessory for the younger generation.</description>

    <title>Sony Launches Xperia L2 For Rs 19,990</title>
    <link>http://www.techtree.com/content/news/13386/sony-launches-xperia-l2-rs-19990.html</link>
    <description>Looking at the success of Vivo and Oppo, Japanese brand Sony has launched its selfie-centric phone in India. Dubbed as the Xperia L2, the phone offers an 8 megapixel front camera. It lets your capture group selfie without missing anyone out. The Xperia L2 lets you to toggle between Portrait Selfie mode and Group Selfie mode, Portrait mode to fit in all your friends in a single click. The main camera is a 13 MP module that promises better low-light photography.
 </description>

    <title>Make Your Old Speakers Wireless With This Tiny Gadget</title>
    <link>http://www.techtree.com/content/features/13385/old-speakers-wireless-tiny-gadget.html</link>
    <description>Gone are the days of conventional music systems. Instead of proper stereo, people prefer to consume music on wireless speakers. The sound quality on most of these wireless speakers may not be very good. However, that's the trade-off consumers put up with for the sheer convenience. If you too wish to jump on the wireless bandwagon without spending much, here's an interesting option. Domestic peripherals company Zebronics has introduced the BT Connect dongle that can turn your good-old speaker system into a wireless one.</description>
